Do you make New Year’s resolutions? I like to make “themes” for my family that will represent the year and make goals surrounding the themes. This year are: connection, purpose, self care, and health! I don’t know about you all, but I’m definitely ready for what 2023 has in store! ✨
I can’t believe the class of 2023 will be graduating in just 5 months! 🎓

This post is a special one for me, so bare with me!
.
I met Leah my very first year doing photography professionally when I did her daughter and foster daughter’s senior photos. Leah and her husband are amazing and long term foster parents that take in so many beautiful children and treat them as their own. Along that foster journey they met these two amazing boys. After having them for a couple years, they’ve decided to adopt them both and that’s when our paths thankfully crossed again when they asked me to do an adoption announcement session!
.
Their adoption was finally finalized today and my heart is so full for their beautiful family! These two boys are in the greatest hands!
How’s 2023 treating you so far?

Sometimes you pray for a miracle, and God gives you two.
.
I’m going to be an aunt again to twins next month 🤍🤍
I will never ever tire of maternity sessions 🌟

PSA for all of my beautiful families out there: while I know that resolutions are in full swing right now, trust me I got them too, please don’t for one second let them hold you back from the here and now. 
Don’t for one moment believe that you are not “good enough” for anything or that reaching a goal will make you more valuable.
Look around you at who matters the most to you—they love you just the way you are. Never hold back from creating those memories, because memories can’t be recreated once the “goal” Is reached. But memories, those will last and will be cherished forever. And trust me, your loved ones aren’t going to look back at their memories or pictures and look at you and think about whether or not your goal was met. They’ll remember you, for you. Just the way you are now. ❤️
So heck yes! Get out there and crush those New Year’s resolutions! But don’t forget to live in the now here and there too along the way 🫶🏼

Want to know the secret to beautiful candid family photos?
Let your children lead the shoot!
.
It’s true! If we want kids to smile and to participate during your session, you have to allow them to be themselves. Let them play, explore, wander, dance, giggle, ask questions, be curious. Let them be comfortable, let them be shy, let them eat snacks. Because in the end, trust that I snapped the best memories that captured your wonderful family in the way that best represents who you all are in this exact moment in time. You’ll love them forever ♥️

Hi, it’s me 👋🏽 swipe to the end to see me with a camera in my hand, and that’s how you’ll usually find me because honestly, being in front of the camera makes me uncomfortable 🙈 
.
Let me tell you a little secret: I really didn’t want to do my birthday portraits this year. I have been letting past insecurities creep back in and haven’t been feeling “my best”. However, instead of letting that get in the way, I decided to not be a hypocrite and remember what I tell my clients—the only thing you’ll regret is NOT doing the photos. Memories can fade, but photos last a lifetime. And you know what? I’m so glad I decided to do them. Doing the photoshoot really is a confidence booster as well as a memory for your loved ones to look back on even after you’re gone. My biggest philosophy: EVERYONE deserves photos and to see how beautiful they really are 🫶🏼 don’t let anything hold you back.

🌟2023 RECAP🌟
.
This year has been a year of growth, learning, collaboration, reflection, and ended with a bit of heartache. But what it’s taught me more than anything is that life is precious. So don’t waste time doing what you don’t love. Document the memories. Work hard. Love harder. And never stop learning. 
.
2023 took me all over Oregon. I got to see the mountains, the snow, the coast, and I even got to chase some waterfalls. I got to spend so much quality time with my sweet little family. I got to capture 20 beautiful weddings and even second shoot a couple too. I got the opportunity to not only host my 4th content day, but also attend a few too and collab with so many talented creatives. I stretched my creative mind on so many fun sessions and met some new friends along the way. I even got to bring my family along to some of these events too. My home studio got so much use this year and I’m hoping to continue that into the new year. I’m so beyond grateful for every single individual that crossed my path this year and supported me in any way. To get the opportunity to make my passion my job is a blessed feeling I could never fully explain. Thank you for every follow, like, share, comment, publication, and booking. The support means the world. 
.
Over all, I’m ready for the new year. Though there were great moments in 2023, there were also a lot of hardships too, but they have only made me stronger and more determined than ever. I hope 2024 brings you all peace, joy, comfort, and drive. Let’s make 2024 our year! And stay tuned for a few announcements in the new year 😉
